---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { getLangFromUrl } from "../../../i18n/utils";

const lang = getLangFromUrl(Astro.url);
---

<Layout title="How to Take Homeopathy" lang={lang}>
  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section
    class="max-w-[1200px] w-full mx-auto px-4 py-[50px] md:py-[100px] pt-[150px]"
  >
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2
        class="font-heading font-bold text-[30px] text-brand-primary uppercase tracking-[0.9px] mb-6"
      >
        How to Take Homeopathy
      </h2>
      <div
        class="font-body text-brand-text text-[17px] leading-[37px] space-y-4"
      >
        <p>
          <strong
            ><span class="underline"
              >RULES FOR FOLLOWING A HOMEOPATHIC TREATMENT</span
            ></strong>
        </p>
        <p>
          For a homeopathic treatment to be as effective as possible, it is
          recommended to:
        </p>
        <p>
          - Keep the mouth as clean as possible when taking the homeopathic
          medicine<br />
          - Do not brush teeth with fluoride toothpaste, do not smoke, and do not
          eat food for at least 10-15 minutes before or 15 minutes after taking the
          homeopathic remedy; you can drink water. You can use Homeopathic toothpaste
          or aloe toothpaste (Vitis brand).<br />
          - Do not drink chamomile tea, or keep it to a minimum and always separate
          from taking the medicine.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong><span class="underline">FORMS OF PRESENTATION:</span></strong>
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong><span class="underline">DROPS</span> = </strong>Put the drops
          in a very clean glass containing a little mineral water. Keep the
          solution in your mouth, ideally under the tongue, for 1 minute and
          then swallow it.
        </p>

        <p>
          <span class="underline"><strong>DRINKABLE AMPOULES</strong></span
          ><strong> = </strong>Put the content of the ampoule in a glass with a
          little water and proceed as above.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong
            ><span class="underline">GRANULES AND TABLETS</span> =
          </strong>It is recommended not to touch them with your fingers.
          According to the medical prescription, keep the granules under your
          tongue until they dissolve.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong><span class="underline">SINGLE DOSE</span> =</strong> They must
          be taken all at once and entirely by the patient. Put the content of the
          entire tube under the tongue until it dissolves.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong><span class="underline">TRITURATIONS</span> =</strong> Powdered
          form that comes in bottles with a measuring spoon. The patient measures
          each dose to be taken with the help of this spoon, and should leave it under
          the tongue until it dissolves.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
